<p>is there a way to change the methods exposed by captains-log? I'm working on a sailsJs project. I need the log levels and calls to be: FATAL\ERROR\WARN\INFO\DEBUG I managed to changed the log levels, by doing this in the config.log file:</p>  <pre><code>var winston = require('winston'); winston.setLevels(   {     crit: 1,     error: 2,     warn: 3,     info: 4,     debug: 5,     verbose: 6   });  module.exports.log = {   level: 'info',   custom: new winston.Logger({     transports: [       new winston.transports.Console(),       new(winston.transports.File)(       {         filename: './.tmp/log.log'       }),     ]   }) }; </code></pre>  <p>but I can't find a way to rename crit, to be fatal, so I can do: <code>sails.log.fatal</code> instead of <code>sails.log.crit</code></p>  <p>thanks!</p>